      "writtenOn": "2018-10-02T18:40:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "+1, there isn\u0027t that great of a solution AFAIK but I would do something like this:\n\nclass AutoComposeDevice {\npublic:\n    AutoComposeDevice(size_t layerCount) : mData(new uint8_t[sizeof(ComposeDevice) + layerCount * sizeof(ComposeLayer)]) {\n        mComposeDevice \u003d reinterpret_cast\u003cComposeDevice*\u003e(mData.get());\n\n        mComposeDevice-\u003eversion \u003d 1;\n        mComposeDevice-\u003etargetHandle \u003d 0;\n        mComposeDevice-\u003enumLayers \u003d layerCount;\n    }\n\n    ComposeDevice* get() {\n        return mComposeDevice;\n    }\n\nprivate:\n    std::unique_ptr\u003cuint8_t[]\u003e mData;\n    ComposeDevice* mComposeDevice;\n};\n\nMaybe with a default constructor too.",
      "parentUuid": "55de7408_af7cf47d",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 222,
        "startChar": 8,
        "endLine": 222,
        "endChar": 20
      },
