      "writtenOn": "2018-10-02T17:14:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We can auto free mComposeDevice on ~SampleApplication if we delcare it as a unique_ptr (it\u0027s cleaner that way IMO)\n\nI.e.,\n\n#include \u003cmemory\u003e\n\nstd::unique_ptr\u003cComposeDevice\u003e mComposeDevice;\n\nand then to allocate it, mComposeDevice.reset(new ComposeDevice)\n\nand then it will do the equivalent of\n\nif (mComposeDevice) free(mComposeDevice)\n\non ~SampleApplication, as the destructor will also invoke the destructor for all class members.",
